data.title: has prince ever lived in new york city?
data.text:
chocolate1

At the ONA Soundcheck at Lincoln Center in 2002, he asked where people were from, so people were yelling out parts of NY and other places. My friend yelled, "NJ", and he said, "I used to live in Rahway, NJ..."

I was just listening to that "track" the other day.

"Love Hurts.

Your lies, they cut me.

Now your words don't mean a thing.

I don't give a damn if you ever loved me..."

-Cher, "Woman's World"

SquirrelMeat

Prince lived in New York with his half sister when he was trying to get a record deal. That stay inspired the Dirty Mind track "Sister".

He also wrote "Leaving For New York" around this time.

.

nurseV
